Bimbo, Embraer, Lan, Marfrig: Latin America Equity Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-04-27T06:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/bimbo-embraer-lan-marfrig-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The MSCI  Latin America  Index rose 0.7 percent to 4,681.79.  Brazil  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS): The world’s fourth-largest airplane
maker reaffirmed its 2011 sales forecast, saying there was no
significant impact from the Japan earthquake on deliveries
planned for the year, according to a regulatory filing. There
may be some delay to deliveries in the second quarter, which
will be made up for in subsequent quarters, the company said.
The stock gained 0.8 percent to 12.61 reais.  Marfrig Alimentos SA (MRFG3)  (MRFG3 BS): Latin America’s second-
largest beef producer plans to sell $500 million of senior
unsecured notes due in 2018, according to a report released by
Fitch Ratings. The shares were unchanged at 16.45 reais.  Chile   Lan Airlines SA (LAN)  : Latin America’s largest airline
by market value reported first-quarter profit of $97.2 million,
according to data posted on the website of Chile’s securities
regulator. The shares added 0.2 percent to 12,945 pesos.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)  : Chile’s biggest retailer by
market value said while it is continually evaluating
opportunities to enter new markets, it hasn’t taken part in any
“official” negotiations, Chairman Juan Cuneo told reporters in
Santiago. The stock jumped 2.7 percent to 5,054 pesos.  Colombia   Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  : Colombia’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer said first-quarter net income increased 95
percent to 42.9 billion pesos ($24 million), according to a
regulatory filing. The shares climbed 0.6 percent to 27,360
pesos.  Mexico  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA MM): The world’s largest bread
maker said first-quarter profit fell 5.7 percent to 1.2 billion
pesos ($103.4 million), the company said in a statement to the
stock exchange. The shares advanced 0.7 percent to 25.51 pesos.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM): The retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire Ricardo Salinas reported
first-quarter net income of 420.6 million pesos, according to a
filing to  Mexico ’s stock exchange. The stock rose 0.7 percent to
510.07 pesos.  TV Azteca SAB (AZTECACP MM): Mexico’s second-largest
broadcast television network said first-quarter net income rose
to 162 million pesos, according to a filing to Mexico’s stock
exchange. The shares gained 1 percent to 8.30 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
